    "created_at": "2026-02-13T23:49:59Z",
    "updated_at": "2026-02-13T23:49:59Z",
    "body": "I have different devShells for each part of the project -- one contains the tools for frontend dev, another one for launching some local servers for testing purposes, and a default one. It seems right now there is no way to see which shell precisely is being used. Regardless if I do `nix develop .` or `nix develop .#js`, the `$name` parameter still prints only `nix-shell-env`, which is useless to see for me. If it printed `default` or `js` depending on which shell exactly it is, then it would be way better. Sometimes I accidentally exit a terminal because I'm in the default devShell via direnv but I thought I was in a nested devShell. It also would help organizing the mess of terminals -- oh, this one I opened for this, and this one for that. For now I can only tell from the relative path what this and that terminal is for",
    "author_association": "NONE",
